disk partition:
fdisk
gparted command - partition - resize/move 


Directory structure:


1.bin  : binary or executable programs,command used by all user
2.boot : bootable files for linux
3.etc	:all system configuration files
4.home	:home directory for all user
5.root	:home directory for root user
6.sbin	:command used by only root user
7.mnt	:for the temporary mounting of filesystems or directories
8.opt	:optional or third party software
9.tmp	:temporary space
10.usr	:user related programm, by default softwares installed in this directory
11.var	:log files
12.sys	:It is a virtual file system for modern Linux distributions to store and allows modification of the devices connected to the system.
13.dev	:It is the location of the device files such as dev/sda1, dev/sda2, etc.
14.proc	:all info about running process with process id
15.lib	:contain kernal modules and shared library


